"Example Values": vip, default account, finance, help desk

"Notes": When a user identity or identities is mapped from a source outside of the message itself it is written to this field. This is where Windows well-known SIDs are resolved.
Numeric value representing the priority of the user account, 1 = low, 2 = medium, 3 = high, 4 = critical

"Example Values": user, computer, well-known sid, group, {any vendor-provided value}
"Notes": Experimental field ** This is still being researched - need to look at what winlogbeats/nxlog may provide in terms of SID resolution in different configurations, and consider different technologies use of “types”
